      "repair_strategy_note": "The repair will define a new type `OrderedPartition n` with sorted list of parts, since `Nat.Partition` does not preserve order. Then define `fromOrderedPartition` (pad with zeros) and `toOrderedPartition` (drop trailing zeros). Prove they are inverse using list operations and the antitone property. The main theorem is an `Equiv` between the sigma type of ordered partitions with length вүӨ N and `NPartition N`. This avoids the missing `Nat.Partition.length` and the ordering mismatch. The proof will use `List.Sorted` lemmas, `List.dropWhile`, `List.reverse`, and `List.ofFn`. The `antitone` condition for `fromOrderedPartition` will be proved by case analysis on whether indices are within the original list length. The `toOrderedPartition` will use `Ој.antitone` to show the dropped list is sorted. The composition proofs will use extensionality for `NPartition` and `OrderedPartition`.",
